FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS
What is Profile Transfer?
The Profile Transfer feature allows people on your account to transfer a profile – including recommendations, viewing history, My List, settings, saved games and more – to their own membership that they pay for. Learn more [https://help.netflix.com/support/122698?g=cd6e63b8-1307-41f2-a68e-faead2cd4717&lkid=URL_HELP_BODY&lnktrk=EVO].
We will never transfer your payment information to the new account, and there is no charge for enabling this feature. Children's profiles and PIN-protected profiles cannot be transferred. All saved games and game progress connected to a profile will move to the new account.

Who is this for?
People move. Families grow. Relationships change. Life happens, and you can make life a bit easier with Profile Transfer.
Unless you turn off this feature, anyone with access to your account will be able to transfer an eligible profile to a new account. Allowing profile transfers will not sign out other devices on your account or block anyone from using your Netflix.

Can I change this setting later?
You’re in control – you can always turn off profile transfers on your account settings page [https://www.netflix.com/YourAccount?g=cd6e63b8-1307-41f2-a68e-faead2cd4717&lkid=URL_ACCOUNT_SETTINGS&lnktrk=EVO].
We're here to help if you need it. Visit the Help Centre [https://help.netflix.com/help?g=cd6e63b8-1307-41f2-a68e-faead2cd4717&lkid=URL_HELP&lnktrk=EVO] for more info or contact us [https://help.netflix.com/contactus?g=cd6e63b8-1307-41f2-a68e-faead2cd4717&lkid=URL_CONTACT&lnktrk=EVO].
